Tigris is an S3-compatible object storage service exposing a single global endpoint at `REDACTED`. Because of its S3 compatibility, the standard `aws` CLI can be used against Tigris by pointing it at the Tigris endpoint and providing Tigris access credentials. In this task you will use the AWS CLI to create a bucket and upload a file to it on Tigris.

